# Project Coding Rules

## Type Checking & Linting
- **Ruff**: Used for linting, import sorting (isort), and code formatting
- **Pyright**: Used for type checking only
- Configuration is in `pyproject.toml`

## Import Order (enforced by Ruff)
1. Standard library imports
2. Third-party imports (`alembic`, `fastapi`, `pydantic`, `sqlalchemy`, etc.)
3. First-party/local imports (`app.*`)

## Type Checking Comments
- Do NOT use mypy-style `# type: ignore` comments
- Use Pyright-style: `# pyright: ignore[errorCode]` when needed
- The `alembic/` directory is excluded from type checking in `pyproject.toml`

## Running Tools
```bash
# Lint and auto-fix
ruff check . --fix

# Check imports
ruff check . --select I

# Format code
ruff format .
```
